cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper is primarily focused on homomorphic encryption techniques and their applications in cryptography. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Information theory is closely related to cryptography and the paper discusses some basic concepts of cryptography. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - Homomorphic encryption involves complex computations and this category deals with the study of computational complexity. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses various applications of homomorphic encryption schemes, which may involve software engineering techniques. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses various encryption schemes and their properties, which may involve data structures and algorithms.
